# Next.js App Router Architecture

## Component Separation
- **Default to Server Components:** All files in `src/app/` are Server Components by default. Fetch data directly in these components using async/await.
- **Client Components:** Only add `'use use client'` at the absolute top of the file if the component requires state (`useState`, `useEffect`) or event listeners (e.g., score logging forms, dashboard charts). Keep client components leaf-nodes wherever possible.

## Data Fetching & Routing
- Use native Next.js `fetch` or direct Prisma queries inside Server Components.
- Use Route Handlers (`app/api/.../route.ts`) exclusively for the AI Engine integration and post-round data submissions.
- Always implement clean TypeScript interfaces for route request bodies and responses.